Step 3: In Linux: open the terminal and run this command("sudo apt-get install postgresql") for "postgresql".

Step 4: After installation enter these commands 
-> sudo passwd postgres
-> enter password as "postgres"
-> sudo su - postgres
-> psql -d template1 -c "ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'postgres';"
-> createdb motus
-> psql motus
-> grant all privileges on database motus to postgres;


Step 7: For postrgreSQL Tool -> sudo apt-get install pgadmin3.

